OL,6,FEvacuated resident Delyth Mitchel told
OL,7,FITV Cymru Wales: "It's not just a
OL,8,Fhouse to us, it's a home. We've been
OL,9,Fhere 35 years since it was built, had
OL,10,Fsome lovely times. Racing around in
OL,11,Fthe morning was one thing but shutting
OL,12,Fthat door was emotional."
OL,14,FJohn Mitchell, 76, whose home sits
OL,15,Fnear the edge of the sinkhole, told PA
OL,16,Fnews agency: "It is frightening, you
OL,17,Fdon't know what will happen with the
OL,18,Fwater going under there and washing
OL,19,Feverything away.
